{{Distinguish|Caffeine}}
{{notability|date=August 2011}} {{primary sources|date=August 2011}} {{Infobox software | name = Kaffeine | logo = [[File:Kaffeine Oxygen.svg|64px]] | screenshot = [[File:Kaffeine 1.0 cat.png|250px]] | caption = Kaffeine title screen on [[Kubuntu]] | developer = The Kaffeine Team | released = ? | frequently_updated = yes<!-- Release version update? Don't edit this page, just click on the version number! --> | programming language = [[C++]] ([[Qt (toolkit)|Qt]]) | operating system = [[Unix-like]] | language = Multilingual | genre = [[Media player (application software)|Media player]] | license = [[GNU General Public License|GNU GPL]] | website = [http://kaffeine.kde.org kaffeine.kde.org] }} '''Kaffeine''' is a [[media player (application software)|media player]] for [[Unix-like]] [[operating system]]s running [[KDE]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cooltechzone.com/2005/03/22/open-source-equivalents-to-windows-programs-choices-choices-choices/|title=Open-Source Equivalents to Windows Programs: Choices, Choices, Choices...|last=Nag|first=Aditya|date= 22 March 2005|work=CoolTechZone|accessdate=2010-11-25}}</ref> By default it uses [[xine]]-lib media framework but also supports [[GStreamer]]. It also supports the use of [[MPlayer]] project's binary codecs for proprietary formats. Kaffeine developers have also produced a [[NPAPI|Mozilla plugin]] to start the player for streaming content over the web.
Features include streaming, [[Digital Video Broadcasting|DVB]], [[DVD]], [[Video CD]] and [[Red Book (audio CD standard)|CD audio]].
